Definition: in full control of your faculties
Example: the witness remained collected throughout the cross-examination; perfectly poised and sure of himself; more self-contained and more dependable than many of the early frontiersmen; strong and self-possessed in the face of trouble
Synonyms: equanimous, noun, attribute, equanimity, poised, self-collected, self-contained, self-possessed, in, full, control, of, your, faculties, the, witness, remained, throughout, cross-examination, perfectly, and, sure, himself, more, dependable, than, many, early, frontiersmen, strong, face, trouble
Category: adj.all
